message.content: The paper does not explicitly mention its arXiv CS sub-category. However, based on the content of the paper, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are: cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). This is because the paper discusses a system that uses sequence-to-sequence techniques for generating questions from paragraphs, which is a common topic in these sub-categories.
